  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-ON-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across five flow-speed operating points. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven achieve required levels and six are conditionally accepted with documented rationale. Decision: Accepted with conditions. NOTE (adversarial): the ContextOfUse description enumerates operating ranges (temperature 36–38 °C, inlet pressure 5–120 mmHg, flow rate 2–8 L/min, rotational speed 2000–4000 RPM, Newtonian blood viscosity 0.0035 Pa·s) in free text, creating the appearance of a bounded envelope, but no hasOperatingEnvelope or hasApplicabilityConstraint link is emitted — the model's formal range of valid use is therefore unspecified per W-ON-02.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-cfd-hemolysis-absolute",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uncertainty-samples",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/grid-convergence-study"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "type": "ContextOfUse",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment. Operating conditions evaluated span blood temperature 36–38 °C, inlet gauge pressure 5–120 mmHg, volumetric flow rate 2–8 L/min, impeller rotational speed 2000–4000 RPM, and assumed Newtonian blood viscosity of 0.0035 Pa·s. Five discrete flow-speed combinations define the simulation matrix. Hemolysis is quantified via the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and compared against an absolute clinical threshold of 0.1 g/100 L.",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "decisionConsequence": "High"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-bench-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench-scale hemolysis experimental comparison — FDA generic pump",
      "description": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against in-vitro hemolysis measurements from the FDA generic centrifugal pump test rig at five operating points. Mean absolute error 0.012 g/100 L; all predictions within expanded uncertainty band (k=2) of experimental measurements."
    },
    {
